wdi2-SP.DYN.TO65.FE.ZS.def: Survival to age 65 refers to the percentage of a cohort of newborn infants that would survive to age 65, if subject to age specific mortality rates of the specified year.
wdi2-SP.DYN.TO65.FE.ZS.name: Survival to age 65
wdi2-SP.DYN.TO65.FE.ZS.source: United Nations Population Division. World Population Prospects: 2019 Revision.
